<br>
However, I created an Ogre to tide over any cravings until Shadows of Luclin and my becoming a Vah Shir, and I spent some time in Innothule overcoming my newness and preaching the ways of Rallos Zek to Frogloks a la Rusty Two-Handed Axe.<br>
<br>
Naturally I sold what little I found in Grobb, and being quite exasperated over Ootok's refusal to give me more than a copper per piece of froglok tad flesh, I shared with her an amusing poem we Oggun's used to sing when we were children.<br>
<br>
I use it now as my teaching language, and I share it here now.<br>
<br>
/gsay &quot;Sittin' in muddy water, Ootok's youngest daughter,<br>
/gsay Looks like her rawhide top has come undone;<br>
/gsay Even more do I soon spot, this troll girl's pretty hot,<br>
/gsay I wouldn't mind making Ootok's grandson!&quot;<br>
: laughs heartily.<br>
<br>
Now I know it is crude, but it IS coming from an Ogre, and I've had a good response to it in Qeynos, that's for sure.<br>
<br>
